[Nouns] bisection, bipartition; dichotomy, subdichotomy; halving; dimidiation.
bifurcation, forking, branching, ramification, divarication; fork, prong; fold.
half, moiety.
[Verbs] bisect, halve, divide, split, cut in two, cleave, dimidiate, dichotomize.
go halves, divide with.
separate, fork, bifurcate; branch off, out; ramify.
[Adjectives] bisected; cloven, cleft; bipartite, biconjugate, bicuspid, bifid; bifurcous, bifurcate, bifurcated; distichous, dichotomous, furcular; semi-, demi-, hemi-.
